Training: [https://forum.faceswap.dev/viewtopic.php?f=27&t=146](https://forum.faceswap.dev/viewtopic.php?f=27&t=146)

Converting: [https://forum.faceswap.dev/viewtopic.php?f=24&t=1083](https://forum.faceswap.dev/viewtopic.php?f=24&t=1083)

If you don't have a good graphics card this process can take a VERY long time (days to weeks -- even with a good one it can take a while depending on the length and quality). The process is relatively easy to learn in a short amount of time.

If you need a leader saying something you would still need an audio file of the leader saying what you want him to say with someone moving their mouth to say it: I.e you would need a video someone who can give a good impression of the person you're deep-faking.

I am more than willing to answer any questions people may have, or to help in the process of deep-faking.
